This paper is about neural machine translation (NMT), which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computational Linguistics" (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of reinforcement learning (RL) in the dual-learning mechanism, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI) and falls under the computer science category of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). The paper also involves training the translation models using feedback signals, which is a subfield of machine learning (ML) and falls under the computer science category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses policy gradient methods to update the models, which is a subfield of neural networks (NN) and falls under the computer science category of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves experiments and empirical evaluations, which is a subfield of software engineering (SE) and falls under the computer science category of "Software Engineering" (cs.SD).
